FAQs
What are the basic requirements to study medicine at Humanitas University?
The basic requirements include a high school diploma with strong grades in science subjects, language proficiency (usually in English), and passing the entrance exam specific to the university.

Is studying medicine at Humanitas University expensive?
While tuition fees and living expenses vary, studying medicine at Humanitas University is often more affordable compared to institutions in countries like the USA or UK. Scholarships and financial aid can also help reduce costs.

How can I apply for scholarships to study at Humanitas University?
You can apply for scholarships through the university, as well as through Italian government programs and private organizations. Qadri-International can assist you in finding and applying for suitable scholarships.

Are degrees from Humanitas University recognized worldwide?
Yes, degrees from Humanitas University are widely recognized and respected globally. Graduates often have the qualifications needed to practice medicine in various countries around the world.

What support can Qadri-International provide for prospective medical students?
Qadri-International offers comprehensive support, including university selection, application assistance, visa processing, and pre-departure guidance, ensuring a smooth and successful journey to studying medicine abroad.
